
[1]cognation

   COGNATION, n.

   1. In the civil law, kindred or natural relation between males and
   females, both descended from the same father; as agnation is the
   relation between males only descended from the same stock.

   2. Kindred; relation by descent from the same original.

   Pride and hardheartedness are of near cognation to ingratitude.

   3. Relation; participation of the same nature.
